---

---

<section id="contact" class="section-pad contact">
  <div class="contact-glow" aria-hidden="true"></div>
  <div class="container contact-inner">
    <p class="eyebrow reveal" style="justify-content: center;">Contact</p>
    <h2 class="h-section reveal" style="--reveal-delay: 0.06s">
      Your engine has a boundary.<br />
      <em class="serif-accent">Let's make it a strength.</em>
    </h2>
    <p class="lede reveal" style="--reveal-delay: 0.12s; margin-inline: auto;">
      Whether you're carrying twenty-year-old extended stored procedures or designing
      new in-engine services, the conversation starts the same way: tell me what your
      database needs to do that T-SQL alone can't.
    </p>
    <div class="contact-cta reveal" style="--reveal-delay: 0.2s">
      <a class="btn btn-primary" href="mailto:kurtkluth@icloud.com">
        kurtkluth@icloud.com
        <svg width="15" height="15" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" aria-hidden="true">
          <path d="M4 6h16v12H4z" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.8" stroke-linejoin="round"/>
          <path d="m4 7 8 6 8-6" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.8" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"/>
        </svg>
      </a>
      <a class="btn btn-ghost" href="https://github.com/kurtkluth" target="_blank" rel="noopener">
        GitHub
      </a>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<style>
  .contact { text-align: center; overflow: hidden; }
  .contact-glow {
    position: absolute;
    left: 50%;
    bottom: -320px;
    transform: translateX(-50%);
    width: 900px;
    height: 560px;
    background: radial-gradient(ellipse at center, rgba(31, 111, 235, 0.2), transparent 65%);
    pointer-events: none;
  }
  .contact-inner {
    display: grid;
    gap: 1.5rem;
    justify-items: center;
    position: relative;
    max-width: 46rem;
  }
  .contact-cta { display: flex; gap: 0.9rem; flex-wrap: wrap; justify-content: center; margin-top: 0.5rem; }
</style>
